d P-component to phosphocholine</article-title><source>Arch Biochem Biophys</source><volume>314</volume><fpage>337</fpage><lpage>343</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">7979374</pub-id></citation></ref><ref id="ppat-0030120-b017"><citation citation-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Omtvedt</surname><given-names>LA</given-names></name><name><surname>Wien</surname><given-names>TN</given-names></name><name><surname>Myran</surname><given-names>T</given-names></name><name><surname>Sletten</surname><given-names>K</given-names></name><name><surname>Husby</surname><given-names>G</given-names></name></person-group><year>2004</year><article-title>Serum amyloid P component in mink, a non-glycosylated protein with affinity for phosphorylethanolamine and phosphorylcholine</article-title><source>Amyloid</source><volume>11</volume><fpage>101</fpage><lpage>108</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">15478465</pub-id></citation></ref><ref id="ppat-0030120-b018"><citation citation-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>de Haas</surname><given-names>CJ</given-names></name><name><surname>van der Tol</surname><given-names>ME</given-names></name><name><surname>Van Kessel</surname><given-names>KP</given-names></name><name><surname>Verhoef</surname><given-names>J</given-names></name><name><surname>Van Strijp</surname><given-names>JA</given-names></name></person-group><year>1998</year><article-title>A synthetic lipopolysaccharide-binding peptide based on amino acids 27&#x02013;39 of serum amyloid P component inhibits lipopolysaccharide-induced responses in human blood</article-title><source>J Immunol</source><volume>161</volume><fpage>3607</fpage><lpage>3615</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">9759883</pub-id></citation></ref><ref id="ppat-0030120-b019"><citation citation-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>de Haas</surname><given-names>CJ</given-names></name></person-group><year>1999</year><articl